author: dolander
msg: Add the IErrorCollector interface.  This interface is implemented by container tags to collect errors from
children who don't render output directly.  For example, the tree renders all the children and on initial
creation of the tree, the treeItems may raise errors.  The Tree tag will collect these errors and then report them
as a group.  This has been checked in to unblock grid development.
To use this interface, a tag implements it.  Children tags call ReportError() to cause the error text to be output.
If there is a parent impelementing IErrorCollector, the error text will be sent to them, otherwise the error text
is written to the current output stream.
